name: Resonant Rise
description:
Delve through the extended history of Minecraftia in Resonant Rise 3!

With the new Era System you can select a lightweight yet deep set of mods revolving around a specific period in history. Visit the time of cavemen in the Primordial Era, dive into magical research in the Medieval Era, or just stick to the present-day Information Era and build an automated factory so you never need to mine again!

There will be six periods of history to choose from in the first full release!

For those of you after a more traditional experience though, check out our Eternity sandbox modes, where the Eras are squashed together to bring you the widest selection of mods from across the modding community, some well-known mods, some deserving of more attention!

Requires Java 7 Update 71 or newer to run. Built for Minecraft 1.7.10 with Forge #1231.

name: Aeternum

!!!UNSTABLE ALPHA PACK!!!

There is no code for this pack. It is currently set to private as it is still being built and balanced. I am looking for testers. If you would like to test it, please tweet me @TigerzFangz.

##Check the change logs BEFORE updating!##

To do this, go to the "Packs" tab and find this mod pack. Click on the "Website" button below the description and scroll to the bottom of the page. Then select the version number that you want to see the change log for.

This pack is currently a custom mod pack being developed by TigersFangs. It is subject to change frequently, and some times drastically. I am still tuning, organizing, and feeling out this mod pack. Please be aware that worlds may or may not be transferable between version updates. I do the absolute best that I can to make sure that ID's stay the same forward and backward, but not all mods in the pack today are guaranteed to be there tomorrow.

SAVES WILL BE BROKEN AT SOME POINT! If you want to avoid this, then do not download an update without first going to the website and checking the version change log at the bottom of the page.

If you have any questions, tweet me @TigerzFangz

Challenge: Beat the Ender Dragon.
  
Do you like resource management? Do you like adventuring? Do you like having tons of different blocks to create unique buildings? Do you also like dying? How about screaming at Minecraft in a rage then throwing your PC out the window? Are you intrigued by the idea of having a heart attack while playing a video game? description:
Explorer's Modpack has been updated to 1.7.10

To encourage risk, you also have two 'bonus' hearts which will always refill, regardless of your food saturation.

There are a lot more mobs, and many more boss mobs, and several dimensions for you to explore. I may add more mods later, but this was nice and stable and I was curious as to what else folks might want to have included as optional.

So, let me know on my G+ page or on the forums.

Enjoy!
Phicksur

name: DarkActiveTEK
description:
A modpack built around the amazing features of GregTech Mod. We love GregTech machines, power storage/generation, and some of the difficult elements it introduces. Unleashed can feel a bit to easy at times. However, we still feel that GregTech takes things to far, so we will be updating configs and removing specific nerfs and "buffing" certain elements unique to GregTech. 

Furthermore, we added mods that we feel are core or important to any good modded server. Mods like IC2, ThermalExpansion, Buildcraft, Thaumcraft, Forestry, ComputerCraft, etc. From that point we sprinkle on other mods that are fun and bring new elements to the game. However, its important that all these other mods aren't overpowered and make things to easy once again. We do this by mostly editing configuration files and if that doesn't work banning specific items on our servers.

The goal of the modpack is to create a difficult but fun modpack that doesn't have that super gridny feeling. So game balance is quite important overall in this pack.

It is multi-dimensional by having specific mods add specific dimensions which gives the pack a more direct adventure path and more avenues of adventure for player. There is no tech (IC2, BC2, etc.), no vanilla biomes, and no lack of adventure.

To access the pack please fill in just your MC name at the link provided in the following post: http://secondarygaming.us/?page_id=43

irc: irc.esper.net #secondarygaming
teamspeak3: secondarygaming.us

name: The Wounded Pack
description: The Wounded Pack is a Private Pack made for Headwound_'s twitch subs. It includes a minimal of mods to clog up the server, but enough mods to make playing just a little more fun.

name: Vaygrim's Chance
description:
Vaygrim's Chance is a 'casual fun' modpack designed for those players who find traditional 'grind' modpacks slow and frustrating. From easy crafting to a balanced mix of technical and magical mods, this pack tries to bring lighthearted fun and adventure back. This pack is the same pack used in the YouTube series "Vaygrim's Chance". 

Head on over to my YouTube Channel (http://youtube.com/vaygrimschance/) to catch the series.

name: Delusions of Adequacy
description:
You will die of hunger. You will die of thirst. You will die of frost. You will die of fire. All before you create your first machines. Welcome to Delusions of Adequacy, a GregTech 5 focused modpack with Hunger Overhaul, Spice of Life, and Enviromine. DoA also features Galacticraft for exploration. And Tinkers' Construct, Tinkers' Steelworks, and EnderIO. Malanced against GregTech for an alternate path that is not 'easier'. Also featuring RotaryCraft, ReactorCraft, and ElectriCraft for a 3rd path.

Tonight we dine in hell!

name: Feed The Bees Swarm
description: Official Feed The Bees Gaming modpack!  Visit http://www.ftbees.com to register and learn how to join. 0.0.1

name: Test Pack Please Ignore
description: This is Test Pack Please Ignore, also known as TPPI and we, the TPPI team, are excited to bring you the FULL RELEASE for the /r/feedthebeast subreddit pack! This mod pack is designed and configured with a slightly more balanced feel to it. This, along with our extensive modlist, allows for more long-term worlds. We’ve brought to you a collection of the very best 1.6.4 mods, including our own utility mod, which you’ll find out about as soon as you begin. So why don’t you click that launch button and start on your adventure!? Remember: You can report all bugs to our github repo at https://github.com/TPPI-Dev/TestPackPleaseIgnore.

name: Wyldcraft
description: A pack focused on creativity and building, but still keeping the difficulty of survival minecraft. WyldCraft features mods made specifically for the pack by the WyldMods team. KitchenCraft, Custom Things, and ToolUtilities allow for that special custom feel. Built by the team over at http://www.twitch.tv/wyld and is the official pack for TwitchTV streamer, Wyld.

name: The Scientist's Toolbox
description:
You are now in a world. A new world. Meaning new beginnings. This Modpack is all about Beginnings, Science and Convenience. The Scientist's Toolbox is a Modpack built for any adventure, any project and almost any activity desired by yourself. 

Your have a new world, laid out in front of you. You could Terraform the land using a variety of builders, magic tools, nukes and more. Or there is the more interesting option of making everything work in harmony. Automation is the name of the game. This Modpack has everything thought out for every decision you make. We even added a Quest Book for those New to Modding and more those who desire a build-up of adventure and tension.

Enjoy yourself! Automate all the things!
-StormyMode and The Toolbox Team :-)
